# Fabrk - Codeium Instructions

**Note:** Customer-facing version. For development instructions with sync workflow, see `.internal/.codeium/cue-dev`.

## Project Overview

**Fabrk** is a premium, enterprise-grade Next.js 15 SaaS boilerplate with a terminal-first aesthetic.

**Stack:** Next.js 15 (App Router) • TypeScript 5 Strict • Tailwind CSS 4 • Radix UI • DaisyUI • PostgreSQL + Prisma • NextAuth v5 • Polar.sh • Resend

## Critical Rules

### 1. Terminal Aesthetic (Non-Negotiable)
- ALL elements: `rounded-none` (never rounded-sm/md/lg/xl)
- ALL UI text: `font-mono`
- Style: Command-line feel with brackets [ ], prefixes >, uppercase

### 2. Design Tokens Only (NO Hardcoded Colors)
```tsx
// GOOD
import { mode } from "@/design-system";
<Button className={cn(mode.radius, mode.font, "text-xs")}>
  > SUBMIT
</Button>

// BAD - will fail pre-commit
<Button className="rounded-lg bg-purple-500 text-white">Submit</Button>
```

**Allowed tokens:**
- Backgrounds: bg-background, bg-card, bg-muted, bg-primary
- Text: text-foreground, text-muted-foreground, text-primary
- Borders: border-border, border-primary

**Banned:** bg-white, bg-gray-*, text-gray-*, #hex, rounded-sm/md/lg/xl

### 3. Component Architecture
- Templates (src/app/templates/): Use Preview/Code tabbed interface
- Docs (src/app/docs/): Use standard templates (ComponentShowcaseTemplate, FeatureGuideTemplate)
- DocsCard: MUST include title prop

